<h3 class="sg-buttons-type-label">Block style button</h3>
<p style="margin-bottom: 2rem">Handy if you want to control the padding around the button from the container. In this case the button fills the container. It still, though, has some minimal padding.</p>
<div style='margin-bottom: 2rem;' class="sg-buttons-constraining-button-demo">
{% include '@atoms/30-button/button.twig' with { button_text: 'Donate now', button_icon_name: 'heart', button_modifiers: ['display-block', 'size-small'] } only %}
</div>

<h3 class="sg-buttons-type-label">Block style button (mobile-only)</h3>
<p style="margin-bottom: 2rem">A special case where the button will only take on the dimensions of the container on mobile.</p>
<div style='margin-bottom: 2rem;'>
  {% include '@atoms/30-button/button.twig' with { button_text: 'Donate now', button_icon_name: 'heart', button_modifiers: ['display-block-mobile-only', 'size-small'] } only %}
